MM-Doc-R1 uses the **Qwen3-8B** backbone model to achieve a 5.0% performance increase when using SPO compared to GRPO. Experimental results show that while SPO improves the Qwen3-4B model by 6.1%, it specifically yields a 5.0% improvement in overall accuracy on the Qwen3-8B model. This gain validates the effectiveness of semantic similarity-based advantage estimation in mitigating bias during multi-turn dialogue training.

